Seal fraud interdiction
-1 3 1 10 67 83 4968 6400 5 2700000 0
4962
Cinder broker enforcers are circulating fraudulent transit seals in the channel lanes, allowing improperly certified convoys to pass through restricted zones. The fraudulent seals are undermining the legal authority of every valid crossing document issued by the registry. The seal clerk has authorized a body count of ten enforcer eliminations as the minimum action needed to collapse the current fraudulent-seal distribution network.
The cinder broker enforcer network has been reduced below operational capacity and fraudulent seal circulation in the channel lanes has dropped sharply. The seal clerk has reissued a corrected transit authorization batch to all affected convoy operators and forwarded an enforcement action report to the Cinder Gate jurisdiction office. The fraudulent-seal incident will be documented in the next quarterly registry audit as evidence for proposed enforcement escalations.

